---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="FAQ — SocialProof" description="Frequently asked questions about SocialProof — the testimonial collection and display tool.">
  <main class="faq-page">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:780px;">
      <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
      <p class="sub">Everything you need to know about SocialProof.</p>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <details>
          <summary>Is SocialProof really free?</summary>
          <p>Yes. The Free plan is free forever — no credit card required. You get 1 widget and up to 10 testimonials. When you need more, upgrade to Pro for $9/month.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <details>
          <summary>How does the embed work?</summary>
          <p>Add a single <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> tag to any page on your website. Your approved testimonials appear automatically in a styled widget. No code changes needed after setup.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <details>
          <summary>What types of testimonials can customers submit?</summary>
          <p>SocialProof collects written text testimonials. Customers fill out a short form with their name, role, company, and a written testimonial. No account needed — they just click your collection link and submit.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <details>
          <summary>Do I have to approve testimonials before they go live?</summary>
          <p>Yes — all testimonials go through your moderation dashboard first. Nothing appears on your site until you approve it.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <details>
          <summary>Can I export my testimonials?</summary>
          <p>Pro and Enterprise plans can export all testimonials as CSV, including the author name, content, rating, and date.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <details>
          <summary>Does SocialProof work with Shopify / WordPress / Squarespace?</summary>
          <p>Yes. The embed is a plain script tag that works on any website. We have specific guides for <a href="/blog/how-to-add-testimonials-shopify">Shopify</a>, <a href="/blog/how-to-add-testimonials-squarespace">Squarespace</a>, and <a href="/blog/how-to-add-testimonials-wix">Wix</a>.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <details>
          <summary>Is there an API?</summary>
          <p>Yes. Pro accounts get full REST API access with API key authentication. You can create, read, and manage testimonials programmatically.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <details>
          <summary>Can I remove the SocialProof branding?</summary>
          <p>Yes — white-labeling is available on the Pro plan and above. The "Powered by SocialProof" badge is removed from your widget.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <details>
          <summary>What happens to my data if I cancel?</summary>
          <p>Your testimonials are yours. You can export everything as CSV before cancelling. We retain your data for 30 days after cancellation in case you change your mind.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <details>
          <summary>How is SocialProof different from Google Reviews?</summary>
          <p>Google Reviews are public and attached to your Google Business Profile. SocialProof lets you collect private testimonials from any customer (not just Google users), display them exactly where you want on your site, and control what goes live through moderation.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
